            "author_info": {
                "name": "Lex Fridman",
                "href": "/profile/Lex-Fridman"
            },
            "answer_text": "Vision-based (i.e., cameras not lidar) self-driving vehicles are already \"affordable\", but they don't work well in the rain, at night, on poorly managed roads, etc.  I think the challenge is not the affordability of the hardware but the effectiveness of the algorithms in the software. I believe we're at least a decade away from the perception and control algorithms being good enough to reach an acceptable level of robustness to the uncertainty of real-world conditions. ",
